      '<h1 class="heading-1">Step 1</h1><p></p><p>In a small pot, stir together the water, oats, and salt. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, then reduce the heat to medium-low. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 2 to 5 minutes, or until the oatmeal is thick and creamy. Stir in a pinch of cinnamon, nutmeg, and/or cardamom, if desired. Remove from heat and let stand for 1 minute. Serve hot with honey or maple syrup, if desired.</p><p></p><h1 class="heading-1">Step 2</h1><p></p><p>To make the Apple &amp; Tart Cherry variation, top with sliced apples, tart cherries, and almonds.</p><p></p><h1 class="heading-1">Step 3</h1><p></p><p>To make the Blueberry &amp; Coconut variation, top with blueberries, orange zest, a scoop of Greek yogurt, chia seeds, and coconut flakes.</p><p></p><p><em>Source: https://www.loveandlemons.com/how-to-make-oatmeal/</em></p>',
